/*           plotEvol.py				*/
/*                                                      */             
/* Compiler: Python                                     */             
/* Dependencies: os, copy, matplotlib, scipy, sys       */ 
/*               math                                   */             
/*                                                      */             
/* Description: Implements simulation for generalized   */
/* reheating model. We particularize it for the         */
/* curvaton model. We evolve the perturbation and the   */
/* background for the curvaton model varying the        */
/* parameters \m_{\sigma}, \sigma(0) and \Gamma_{sigma},*/
/* for the curvaton scalar field(s), radiation,         */ 
/* dark matter, neutrino and dark radiatiom fluids.     */
/* We evolve the perturbations for separate             */
/* cosmologies and compute the correlation matrix for   */
/* any perturbation degree of freedom; we then compute  */
/* the correlation matrix for the curvature perturbation*/
/* for each species and then the correlation matrix     */ 
/* between all the isocurvatures.                       */
/*                                                      */
/* We plot the evolution of densities, perturbations    */
/* and the power spectra. We plot the dependece of the  */
/* curvaton parameters  (\lambda, \alpha and r) varying */ 
/*  \m_{\sigma}, \sigma(0) and \Gamma_{sigma}.          */             
/********************************************************/             

